French Prime Minister Jean-Marc
Ayrault said he considers the situation of the euro preoccupying
and that after the Greek election, European leaders must be up
to the challenge of stabilizing the common currency, Agence
 France  Presse reported.  European leaders must rise to the challenge of solving the
issue of debt, and debt management, Ayrault said in Nantes,
western France, according to AFP. Ayrault also said there should
also be growth measures taken, AFP added.  To contact the reporters on this story:
